HOBJkUUn1ao.title: BEAT THE CHEF: MYSTERY BOX CHALLENGE (RICE) | Sorted Food
HOBJkUUn1ao.description:
AD | Beat the Chef is BACK. And this time Baz is taking on Chef Ebbers in a Mystery Box Challenge that celebrates the humble rice grain. 

To swot up on their rice knowledge, we sent them both to learn from a rice farmer and rice breeder in Italy. BASF’s agriculture experts helped to explain just how much work grows into creating the grain we so often take for granted! So, whose dish will best celebrate everything they learnt in the paddy fields? Who will take the win on this occasion…?

Want even more? You can catch us Behind the Scenes with the experts here: https://youtu.be/sO6xVnfnito 
Get Ben’s recipe here: https://sortedfood.com/summer-green-risotto

sF6TcQbRnpc.title: How to make Pancakes at home... Like a Chef | Sorted Food
sF6TcQbRnpc.description:
In this series our chefs show you their methods and cheats for cooking some of the internet’s most requested dishes at home. Today it’s PANCAKES!

Ben shows us how to make incredible Crepes and big old fluffy American Style Pancakes and shares a pro-tip so you’ll never need follow a pancake recipe again!

We know that times for all of us are a bit tight right now, so we want to share creative ways to cook at home with leftovers and staple cupboard ingredients. 

FLUFFY PANCAKES RATIO:
1: Part Eggs
1: Part Milk (g and ml pretty much weigh the same)
1: Part Flour (plain/all purpose)
Salt (+ Pepper if you're going savoury)
Pinch of Baking power
1 Tbsp butter for lacing or frying

CREPES RATIO:
1: Part Eggs
1: Part Milk (again, g and ml weigh pretty much the same here)
0.5: Parts Flour (plain/all purpose)
Salt (+ Pepper if you're going savoury)
1 Tbsp butter for lacing or frying

Wanna become an awesome home cook? Sign up to our Sidekick app and be the hero of your kitchen: https://bit.ly/3tfFgsR

x5kjO-rTocs.title: Mystery Box Challenge | Making a 100 Layer Lasagne!! | Sorted Food
x5kjO-rTocs.description:
#WithMe - Anyone here a fan of a lasagne or lasagna recipe? Well today, your dreams have come true because James has a Mystery Box Challenge where Mike will try to make a lasagne with 100 LAYERS using unused ingredients from our studio kitchen. This masterpiece was invented by Chef, Mark Ladner in 2009 for the New York City restaurant, Del Posto. That’s 50 layers of fresh pasta, in between another 50 layers of sauce. Sounds easy, right?

Watch now to see if Mike manages to pull it off in this self-isolation special!

*Don’t panic, no ingredients were wasted in the making of this video. The result is currently frozen for Ben and James to try in person!*

Want to know how to make a lasagne? Try our lasagne recipe:
https://bit.ly/2x0cUsk

CT_cTHJPQCs.title: 2 Chefs Review CBD Food & Drink Products! | Sorted Food
CT_cTHJPQCs.description:
CBD products have been trending through the food and healthcare industry over the last five years - from CBD Tea, to CBD Gummy Bears, CBD oil, vape and even CBD creams. But our question is, are the food ones any good, or is drug culture still driving the marketing behind these products and overshadowing the widely recognised health benefits? In this episode, we open up the conversation to hear each other’s opinions - and we taste-test a few weird and wonderful products along the way!

hL_7OgRNeHY.title: Beat The Chef: Ultimate Potato Battle | Sorted Food
hL_7OgRNeHY.description:
#Ad | Get ready because in this episode, we’re celebrating one of the world’s most staple crops: the potato, by challenging Mike to see if he can ‘Beat The Chef’ using this hero ingredient.

But first, Mike and Ben are sent on a journey to dig into the history of the potato to find out where it came from and how farmers use smart technology to produce the hearty spud on a global level. Along the way, they meet Angela Clutton, a food writer and historian, and Jacob Van Den Borne, a top potato farmer from the Netherlands.

Place your bets, because this is an ultimate cook-off that gets very competitive. Comment below to let us know who is your real winner and why!

Grab Ben’s recipe here: https://bit.ly/3bM6P1r 
Grab Mike’s here: https://bit.ly/2UA0Tmp

Wra4YirEI7Q.title: 2 CHEFS attempt a 3 COURSE EASTER FEAST in 3 HOURS!! | Sorted Food
Wra4YirEI7Q.description:
Easter, a time for friends, family and most importantly: GOOD FOOD. In this episode, our Chefs give you their guide to Easter by cooking up three delicious, Easter inspired dishes that’ll get you into the foodie spirit!

Our mouth-watering menu starts with Edible Bird’s Nest Asparagus Soup, followed by the main course, Bunny and Carrots, finished by Hot Cross Creme Egg Doughnuts. But is this a feast that’s fit for our three little bunnies, Barry, Jamie and Mike?

So whether you’re spending your Easter Sunday at home on a video call with loved ones, or if you’re bunkering down with your household, we hope that this episode lifts your foodie spirits for when you’re next able to host a dinner party!

7q0WVzKi2KQ.title: Taste Testing the Latest Food Trend Products | Vol.5 | Sorted Food
7q0WVzKi2KQ.description:
Calling out to all the serial snackers out there: if you love to snack and discuss food trends, then this is the episode for you! When you’re on the run and don’t have the time to sit down for a proper meal, we all have a trusty snack that we tend to turn to. But do we ever choose these products based on their health claims, and if we do, how convinced are we that they’ll do the job? Watch on to hear our thoughts as we munch through some snacking treats.

You can find out more about the gadgets/ingredients we've reviewed in the links below. Pr4zrQxkK6g.description:
Stop what you’re doing because this episode is an Ultimate Fusion Chef Battle! Drawn at random, our Chefs were given two cuisines that they must fuse together in a cooking battle. Ben was given German and Vietnamese, while James was given Peruvian and Filipino. Sounds easy, right...?

We'd love you to come and hang out with us on Instagram at 4.30pm every week day where our chefs will be on hand to answer any foodie questions you have at this time and just create a fun place for us to all be together. 

Apologies for lack of recipes at this time... whilst we aim to get them up... perhaps these similar flavours and ideas will inspire:-
Adobo Chicken: https://bit.ly/2wru1D2

WNRjfop8FT4.title: Fruity Ice Granita Recipes - Frozen Italian Dessert. #spon
WNRjfop8FT4.description:
In the summertime when the weather is fine there is only one thing you need. Granitas! This recipe is a foolproof and delicious take on the epic frozen Italian dessert.

Make it yourself: http://bit.ly/GourmetGranitas
Tropical Carrot Cake:
With the saved orange pulp, a great use is to combine 250g of it with 175g of plain flour, 175g soft brown sugar, 1 tsp of baking powder, 2 eggs, 100ml of sunflower oil and a handful of chopped up dried mango to give you a tropically spiced carrot cake batter that only needs baking off for 50 minutes at 160℃ to give you something really quite special.

For more information on Kenwood products and the PureJuice juicer seen in this video head here: http://bit.ly/KenwoodWorld3

gpyGJwgyNcA.title: Crispy Chilli Lamb and Butterbean Hummus Recipe #Ad
gpyGJwgyNcA.description:
Another fantastically simple and speedy Lamb recipe cooked on the farm... this time with an Italian twist.

A smooth and delicious variation on hummus made with butterbeans creates the perfect bed for stacks of crispy fiery chilli lamb. Topped off with fresh tomato, parsley and olive oil all you'll want to do is mop it all up with the charred bread.

Get the full recipe at http://sortedfood.com/crispylamb

When you're buying your lamb, keep your eyes peeled for a quality mark, for example we have the Red Tractor Logo in the UK. It ensures animal welfare and reliably sourced meat.

Check out loads more recipes and lamb inspiration from the LambSoc here: https://www.facebook.com/LambSoc

olqJnASwrRs.description:
Welcome to another awesome Rennie Mystery Box Challenge!

This video contains a paid for promotion, but that’s not the mystery ingredient! 

Have any of you seen this ingredient? It was new to ALL of us! Although the flavour was relatively familiar, the actual mystery item was very different to the more common place fruit. That didn’t hold us back though, we used it in two ways, a gorgeous homemade marmalade and in a tower of cake decorated in a naked style! Watch to find out what it is and how we get on… we promise we don’t take any clothes off!!

Get the full recipe with step-by-step instructions here: http://sortedfood.com/nakedcake

zSBbzLhmO4o.description:

oQKjd0MzQwM.title: The Hot Dog Burger | #BeatMyBurger Ep. 7
oQKjd0MzQwM.description:
The base of a crusty white roll glazed and baked with egg white for the extra shine kick starts this German-inspired burger. Next up plenty of German mustard-spiked sour cream and then the star of the burger... the flattened German pork meatball spiced with flavours from the classic Lebkuchen biscuit and covered in schnitzel-style golden fried breadcrumbs. Topped with slithers of grilled salami, then raw crunchy red cabbage followed by tangy sauerkraut. Before the lid of the shiny roll, the burger is completed with a split, char-grilled Bavarian frankfurter and sweet caramelised onions.

Get the full recipe here: http://bit.ly/1vnEgNN

Check out our Collab with Flula here: http://bit.ly/1tmqojL

vAPRZj1J1xY.title: The Bloody Mary Burger | #BeatMyBurger Ep. 6
vAPRZj1J1xY.description:
A lightly toasted english muffin stands proudly on the plate topped with a spoonful of tangy vodka and tomato braised onions. Above this, nestles a vodka flambéed double stack of beef patties seasoned heavily with Worcestershire sauce and celery salt, sandwiching slices of oozing cheese. Topped with pickled matchsticks of crunchy celery, and plenty of hot and fiery Tabasco and chive mayonnaise capped with the lid of the toasted muffin. With a chilled glass of Bloody Mary on the side this’ll get your day off to a proper start!

Want the full recipe for this: http://bit.ly/1F7TgSx

Check out the Burger Chat with HeyClaire that sits behind this creation: http://bit.ly/1tjdoul

4NqVmt3TsB4.title: The Hella-Big Burger | #BeatMyBurger ep.3
4NqVmt3TsB4.description:
A black pepper and fresh thyme criss-cross baked jacket potato forms the burger ‘bun’ here. This lacto-free and bread free burger is not for the faint-hearted! An impressively-sized beef burger seasoned with mustard powder and draped with a sunny side up fried egg sits in between. To cut through the richness enjoy slices of juicy beef tomato, some homemade cider vinegar pickled red onions infused with star anise, cloves and peppercorns and a generous dollop of creamy dill mayonnaise. You may need a knife and fork… but you sure won’t want to leave any on the plate! It's elegantly trashy!

We’re on a quest to find the internet’s ultimate burger and this suggestion came from top YouTuber and all round brilliant creator, Grace Helbig. Check out the video here: http://bit.ly/1wJoVZk

You can grab the recipe here: http://bit.ly/1FZ0o6Y

kYNeHbxRc1c.title: The Sushi Burger | #BeatMyBurger ep.2
kYNeHbxRc1c.description:
The Sushi Burger: Crispy golden sushi rice ‘buns’ flavoured with the sweetness of mirin sandwich fresh tuna and wasabi patties. Ribbons of crunchy and vibrant rice wine vinegar pickled cucumber and radish turn these sliders into a mouthwatering 'LA meets Japan'-inspired burger. Finished with a drizzle of a salty orange and soy glaze and plenty of tangy citrus yuzu mayo, these sliders will definitely take some beating.

We’re on a quest to find the internet’s ultimate burger and this suggestion came from top YouTuber and seriously awesome human being, Fleur De Force.
